\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Could you tell me how many years you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh 
where I was born. Well - I can always remember - there was a - a brother older than I was - I should be - I should be - five or six years there. I can't just tell you - to time, he was older than me and he - he was older and I can on - only remember - he 
d
ied, this baby, and - and - he were about eleven months I think, I've heard me mother say, and - I don't re - member anything only about the vicar. And I can see him - I've always seen him since, and he knelt down on the floor. And - and the baby - and ba
b
y - and he was younger than I was, so - I was - I should be there five years. Five or six. And then - we moved - just a bit higher up, to my - and we come here - what, I - I was only - ten - when we come here. So - I couldn't have been - on Lane Ends abou
t
 - five - the first house and six at the old - five at the other altogether, we come here at ten. The tenants that - they - lived in here, they built it. And another family next door built that. And in the meantime I think that - they called him Bob Wrigh
t, he bought one - he - did he buy one - up at top of Lidget. Mm. And we come - we come here, I should be ten or eleven when I come here, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you lived in the house where you were born at Lane Ends, then you lived in another one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 At Lane Ends, yes. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Then you moved to this one when you were ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you live here until you were married then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you must have lived here about fourteen years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Some - yes, mm, fourteen years, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you remember why your mother and father made these moves from one house to the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Did - why they moved? Well - well I do like now, I remember our - like the first house - we had the fish shop on there - at that time I can remember, I
 were only little. But I've only heard me mother tell. And - they - with this fish shop - and the neighbour next door to where we was on Lane Ends, the - lavatory got stopped up, they were Tinklers as they call them you know, got stopped up, and - me moth
e
r got notice to flit from there, the - lady next door said that we'd been putting - me mother had been putting fish heads down. But they never found any fish heads. But she told the landlord and he gave me mother notice. And - she says, well I've never pu
t
 no fish heads down, and - he says, well Mrs Fittle says either - fish heads - it's a salmon tin that you've put down. She says, well in fact we don't eat salmon. So she says, I haven't put a salmon tin down. Well however me mother says she's to get out i
n
 a hurry, and she got into a Haggas's - the mill, but they got one because me father worked there. And those little houses were bad to get then as it happened. And I can always remember that. And that when the landlord came - for the rent - it were monthl
y
, and - it must have been only half a crown a week, of course happen that'd be a lot in them days, I don't know, were ten shillings a month, and she paid him all with pennies and ha'pennies from fish shop. And she told - I know she did shout a bit. She mu
st have told him - to count it and see if it were right, but she said he never bothered, he got it all in his pocket and on his way. Then that was - I do know that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 That was at the fish shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, and that was - when we had the fish shop, th
en me father worked down at the mill, and then of course - there were - I - I had a brother then and it was only - two small - rooms and so me mother must have been - I don't and - you don't get told when you're so small, you aren't - don't under - for an
other house and that's why we came here, you see, so - and that - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 The second house that you moved into, was it one of Haggas's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, that was one of Haggas's, on Mount Pleasant there. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Was the first one a Haggas's house as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, it was a private - it - belong - the lady that lived next door, this man had married her and he were - they'd married late in life you see but they went to live at Crossroads. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You moved from the second house to this one because it was bigger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes. YES? Yes, yes, was more room you see, there - just - and I know we - had - we got our first piano there at that house up those steps. I remember it were - such a tussle to get it up but - they - they did manage in those days
. That's about - like - yes, mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you moved to this house was this owned by someone or did you buy it, did your parents buy this house when they moved here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When we - we - we - when we come back here - I came back to me father you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 But at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 My mother bought it. Yes. Yes, yes, off the builder, off - off Robert Wright. Yes, me mother brought the house. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you just have the one brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh I had two brothers, they're both - younger than me but that they're both dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So one died when he was eleven months old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Oh - that was a - the - the baby, these other two came later, he'd have been next to me if he'd have been here then - about - I think he was about - I was about three or something I've 
heard me mother say, when he was born. And - there were two and a hal I think years between - our Ellis and our Fred, our Fred were youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How much younger than you were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 They - they were younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 About five years would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well five years between - me and our Ellis. And six years between Ellis and Fred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you're quite well spaced out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, but - that - baby that died was between me and Ellis you see. That - that time. But - I don't remember - like - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You didn't have a sister then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no, I hadn't a sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you know how old your father would be when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3417516\charrsid11482206 When I were born? E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
h I don't. I think - I think I've heard me mother say - I'm sure me mother - stopped at home - 't
il she were twenty-eight. I've heard her say. Remember telling her - me - that - when she got married - she dressed them all in new clothes. These - two - three - sister - younger sister}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3417516\charrsid11482206 s, me
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206  Aunt Alice and Aunt Ada. Mm. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Your mother and father would both be about twenty-eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you know where your father came from? Was he a local man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, Oakworth, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 He'd always lived in Oakworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 At - and they were - any - h
e were right up the - Bridge Street there up at the top. And he just had another brother - but he was older were me Uncle John. And they lived at the top of James Street, their family, well there's only - Wilfred Wiley now living and he lives on Church St
reet. And he's eighty some, he's older than me. And I'm only - the only one that is Riley. Mm.
