\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 At school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well - she went to the school but - she were only ill a week or two. And - I can remember - we - I should be - I weren't old, and we walked from the - village at Lower Bank o
ut at - they called her Edith Marcham. And - and she - she were about the age of me. And I - I - her sis - she had a sister living, that married Hedley Peel, the coalman. Well his wife - were a Marcham, this girl's sister that I'm telling you about, and -
 
they lived up at Lower Bank, the family, then up there, and - I don't know what - I can't remember what she died of but she were about the age of me, she were a nice girl and we used to play altogether in - the school - in the school yard, and there was a
 
ser - she was buried at bottom of church yard, here, I remember it as plain as the day. And - we all lined up, the scholars, down the school yard. I can see 'em now, and walking down and they took her into the church first you see, and - I - and - and whe
n
 they take - I think we went in the church, scholars, but we didn't go down to the - I think we come back to school. But - all the - scholars went, but for the - I think the little babies, then because it were for all - what there were at that time, there
'
s some went down to - they called it board school, but it was the Wesleyan school, I don't think - the West Riding would pay for it, I suppose at latter end - but it was always the Wesleyan school. Mm. And - and that were - the only one I remember. And - 
a
nd I know - it were - we - I think we had a hymn in school, before we went - into the church. I don't know whether any of the others ever remember but happen not be so many of 'em left. And what had been matter with the girl I don't know, she - she wasn't
 ill long so - you know, the - could be - two or three of - half a dozen of a family I daresay, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Were they in mourning? Can you remember what they were dressed in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 We - no, I don't. I think - the - the family were mostly in black, but we ju
st went - I know the schoolmaster said if we had - if we - I - it must have been in - warmer weather, could we go in a white pinafore, we wore pinafores in those days. If you hadn't a white - little white frock or - we - and - as far as I can remember we 
all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3878432\charrsid11482206  tried to have a little white po}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
ny on. And I know me mother used to make me a little cotton frock or two and I think I should have a - just a little white - they were only plain, up and down and sleeves, you'd to - you hadn't to be - fancy. And - I can j
ust re - remember that. But I can't remember anything about the service but I'm sure we went in the church. But we - I know we didn't go down - to the bottom, but - nosey I suppose, when school closed a lot of us went - to look - at - at the grave, yes, I
 
think we'd taken a penny for - for - some of 'em, the teachers, they got some flowers, mm. And I think the scholars if they could - they could take a ha'penny and a penny, and - that were a lot in them days you know. MM. And so that were all I remember ab
out - but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you remember how they came, did the family come in coaches?
