Yes, we'd go tot Newsholme Dene you know, down - Goose Highway and come back up Crags through - here. That were through Newsholme and then - me grandmother's - at Bobbin Mill at the bottom at Newsholme there. That was Bobbin Mill then and - we sh
ould call there you see, we went - many a time down into bottom like into Newsholme Dene. But not really - picnicking because - well we used to - to go in and - visit time. Go bilberrying down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What would you go in to, was there a caf\'e9 there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh - well - I don't say that - we didn't stop for food. No. Just go for the wal Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would this be sort of any Sunday or would it be a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I think any time I think - during week or any time. I don't think - Bank Holidays, I don't th
ink they were ever observed much in those days. They were just - and - and the - holidays, proper holiday - were three - same was Feast holiday, they were only Saturday, Monday and Tuesday. I remember that four days. And - some - people were fortunate - g
ot to go away, but I don't remember - ever getting to go like. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No farther than Newshollme?
