Oh no. I think - I think that - well our Fred - our Fred were - our Ellis used to say were petted. He were six years - between 'em like, they used to just be - and me mother'd put her foot
 down and - and it were all right again like it - there it - these little just bits of jumbles up in families isn't there like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 But you didn't feel any closer to one than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, they - no, no, I - and I - I don't - there were - it were soon forgotten, owt that - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you were a little girl who did you play with mainly your brothers or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Little girls round on - on here like, same as I tell you - Jennie were my friend. Mm. Mm. And - I don't know as - if - there wer
e any more about with - didn't seem to - I had to do my music lesson, well I didn't get much - time playing out. I don't say we didn't get out a bit but - I used to grumble and say so and so - can play out. Mm. And then - there were - when I were growing 
up a bit bigger - I know I - me father told me I had a to help me mother. And I had to learn to wash up and that, I used to do all - all dusting upstairs. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So when you did find time to play out where would you play out mainly? Would it be in the bac
k yard, or in the garden or in the street? Or at other homes? Was there a field somewhere where you could play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, I think we - where - I went to Jennie's now and again and she'd come here, and when it were light weather, well there weren't much - 
where to - to play only - streets, but you know there weren't - traffic like there is today. There were no houses on that other side of road. On church Street there. There were fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would you play in the fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - I - no, there were - ha
ymaking fields. Only when it were feast, our holidays, there were a fair come - over those fields. Yes. Yes, well as far as I can remember - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you played out with Jennie and the other little girls, what games would you play can you remember any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well I know we used to have a - a lot of ball - I had a lot of balls, yes, rubber balls. And - there used to be these here - we used to call it - play hobbs, you know, you'd - run to one and - run to another, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Like rounders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Aye, ay
e, rounders, mm, that's - we call - they used to let us go down at school yard a bit. But not so much. Because windows got broken and it were nobody. But - we generally - but I think - as a rule, I think I - I think our family - stayed in, looking at book
s and drawing, boys or - doing bits of things like that. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played out, would your mother be very cross if you did get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - well, she didn't like us - I - I didn't - I never liked meself dirty, I 
were - oh I can't bear - be all sticky, I'd wash meself - I used - used to say I used too much soap, I say, nay, I never do. I always - couldn't feel sticky. No. I never have yet, all me life I couldn't bear if I - didn't feel clean. No, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you never got into trouble about being dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, no. I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you did go out were you free to play with anyone you pleased, or were there children that your mother didn't like you playing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1527130\charrsid11482206  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh - no, no, I don't think there were any round about, we - there were some down the street here. We played all together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And there was no one who she disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, no, I don't think there was round about here. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I was asking about having anything special for tea on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And you said that you'd sometimes have a little boiled ham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well I used to like a tin of - a - a tin of salmon. YES. And - oh I love - salmon, and - and me mother wouldn't have it, you know, she never ate it. But she'd - let us have it, we could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you got married at first up until 1919 did you make all the bread yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, now I don't - now I don't think I started - 'til he came back after the war, I think I'd had a - I had baked bits you see, but I thin
k me mother gave me a lot, me mother baked her bread. But - yes, but after then I started, oh yes, started baking me own bread. Yes. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever make your own jam?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And what about pickles, did you ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Pickles? Well, only happen - a bit of onion and cucumber together. Didn't make tem - those to stand you know what I mean. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever make your own wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What about beer, did you make beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No. We - oh - brought up amongst it, me mother did but I - I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What about any medicines for the children or for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes - some eggs and - some - rum or something, it were left to stand, I forget, I made it - I made it for children when they were growing up. So
me - a - a drop of rum in, but it weren't much, it weren't flavoured but they said it were a good thing, for growing up children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well I daresay, yes - but like they were - plenty of 'em weren't there. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And you would bottle them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, just a few. I used to - bottle beetroot. Yes, I boiled beetroot many a time. Because they liked it on their bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You never had a sufficiently large garden to grow vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you would buy your own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Mm, yes, mm. If I could get them local I did do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever buy tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you buy prunes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And - and steep 'em myself, yes. Have some for tea today. I'd forgotten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You did it then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, and I - I always steep 'em overnight. She ste}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1527130\charrsid11482206 ep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206  'em yesterday, I just forgot when we were mentioning prunes. She'd found 'em in cupboa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1527130\charrsid11482206 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 d and they'd been - in a box 
- such a long while. She looked at 'em and they're quite nice, found 'em - oh she says, we'll have a fresh - tea tomorrow. I says, well you'll be short of cream. Says, well it'll have to be custard. We only get cream at weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever keep any livestock, either hens or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - years back, yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When you and your husband were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, up the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1527130\charrsid11482206 re, at - at the top when we - w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 e he come back from the first world war - there was like a - a croft attached to it you see, and
 he - had half a dozen hens. And me father had some out here. He gave him two. And he - aunt at Newsholme gave him two and - and uncles gave him two. He got set up. He - he loved it, and that - he - he loved his time up there - at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And he he looked after them himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, he - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How many times a week would you eat meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 In meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How many times a week would you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Mm. Well I got - Sunday roast and it - and then it did - he used to generall
y get enough for - for Monday and Tuesday. But we - I generally had a - a bit of meat every day unless some bacon. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever have tinned meat.? You said you had boiled ham, would that be a tin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Mm. Not - not a - right lot. I - I have - boiled - tongues and stuff meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 They wouldn't be tinned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, no, we - I - we might get a little one - emergency a chance someone call, I always wanted to have a tin of something in, you - for make a bit of something but - this last few years I've done me own. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 But in the period before 1919.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would you ever buy little tins of things then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Just - you know, a - bit of salmon or - mm - or - a small tin of tongue. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you ever remember having any extra meat from poaching? Did you ever know anyone who shot rabbits on the moors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Eeh, I - I - I might have had one or two. From - me uncles that lived over that way, but I - I think I did there, but I never paid for anything, because - we weren't
 fond of - of rabbits. Me mother - me mother hadn't - liked it, they never - but I know I have had one or two since I've had a home because - I - I've cooked 'em in a casserole. But - I've never been - it's never been our habit to buying them you know. Mm
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you when you were married at first ever go short so that your husband and children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no. We all served alike. We did at home as well. We all shared alike,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would your husband have a larger helping of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Never 
- he's never been a big eater, not like some - young men are. No he hasn't. But he gets as much as he wants. And - it isn't that it's - being stinted from him you know but - if - he says - if he's a bit - I said, well what you don't want leave. But - this
 last few years - I will say he's eaten better. Since he's retired. I believe he - he's eaten a bit more. But not as it matters like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When Hilda started to sit at the table for her meals was she allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well they never have talked a lot, they've - just been content to - get their - their own food like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Was she allowed to choose what she wanted to eat from what was cooked or did she have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 They got a bit of everything, but - I don't believe
 in 'em - if they try it and - you see, if it doesn't agree with them you can stop giving 'em it but - they - say - that they don't want it sometimes can't they. Well it's only ten past four. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What would you say if she left some food uneaten on her plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well - I didn't say anything - as a rule because they did - well nearly always they - eat it all up, but I - if they - I didn't force 'em because it does 'em no good forcing 'em. 'Cos I think it - it's better - it's better to throw it out tha
n force 'em, because they're - you're - their littles tummies isn't always same, same as your own - you don't always feel as - as sometimes when - I feel as I could eat a lot more but - and then if I got it I shouldn't want it, I think it's - just a thing
, if you see it it's something that you like, you think you'll have a bit more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would she have to wait until the things on the table, for example the salt, was offered to her, or could Hilda ask for the salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 She could ask for a bit more, please, if they want you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What about a second helping, could she always ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well, not always, no, no, hasn't been but - but - if we want more because of - I've all - we've always been used to having a pudding as well. I
t's - it's - each day some sort or - or other, like well - the - the vegetable course - like I - I think you - they don't want as much when you have a pudding. We've always been brought up for a - pudding every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you insist that she held her knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Oh yes. Yes. Mm. They know how to - they knew how to set table out, and I know doctor come once when - it were when I were - there were Mary and Hilda, and I was in bed and she were - he says, w
ell I'm pleased you girls know how to lay the table. Mm. So - of course they - they liked - that sort of work, you know, if they like they carry on with it don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would you allow Hilda to bring a toy or a book to the table when it was a mealtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well, no, I - I didn't like that. No. Just have their meal and then go - have their book after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When was she allowed to leave the table, did she have to ask if she could leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh well, they - they - they - they'd sit while they saw and then - please can - may I leave the table. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would they have to wait until you'd all finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - not particularly if - we were a bit longer and we thought they were getting restless. We let them leave the table.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did all th
e family present for the meal sit at the table? Would you all sit up to the table or would perhaps your husband sometimes have his tea in front of the fire, something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - since w've been ill this last time it's never been done before, I
've sometimes sat away - because I can't eat quickly. And I've - I've thought - I've a - annoyed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 In the period before 1919 you always all of you sat at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When your children were young did you feel that there was a ri
ght way and a wrong way of bringing up children? Did you have definite ideas about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well I don't - I don't know, how I - I just thought that - I brought 'em up as I thought were right, I - you see - if they were - to start - they wouldn't - if the
y'd happen start - same as you've seen some, having a giggle or something, well, if I just say, now drop that, they know not to - there's sometimes that - same as when Pauline and Valerie's come you know the - they're a - they've a bit more off now than t
h
ey had in our - when ours were younger, you know and - they say - go - they'll say - look, they've said - when being little they always called me nan-nan you see, and our Pauline does yet, and then she'll say grandma sometimes. She'll say - oh - mummy - n
an-nan you know - said this, and her mum says, now then was you doing something wrong? No, no. But they're so quick today. I don't know - I'm glad they are quick you know but - they're just a bit too - too - yes, aye, they're -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up children or did you have different ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I don't think so, he - he said - same as me, the - if they're brought up as we are they should be - in right - position.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would you discuss it between you, you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well, he - he'll have said to me, do you think that - our - our - Hilda - is - well - well like, well enough for - she seemed to have a bit of a stomach - is that right for her - meal you see. And I says, oh well, I wouldn't - give h
er anything if I though - wouldn't pass her - to make her sick or owt, we hadn't discussed it a lot because we've let them have - what they fancied if it was on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I don't think - anything, if they weren't - right well, we used - used to have the doctor. Mm. YES.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Was your mother alive when the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - Valerie - Mary and Hilda yes. Yes, because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How often did you see her, when you were living up at Lidget?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh - oh well she didn't come much up Lidget, she come up - more up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And then for a period of about two years you lived with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Yes, oh yes. Yes. Yes. Mm. Like all the - the war time the same 
as - brought up here well like - of course Mary - as I say to her, she - called me father - dad-dad you see, did Mary, she were a long time but - they've all be they - grew up all right like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever ask her advice in bringing up the children, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well - I only use - use - used to say like - same as about if - do you think they're all right like? She says, well, if they - get some - plain food they'll - they'll be - take no fault. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you and she have the same ideas about this? Did you agree on bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Oh yes, because - there was - nothing - that were - were wrong that she meant as said like - she wasn't strict nor nothing like that but - you knew how far - you knew how far to go like. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You tell me that your mother-in-law died just after your husband joined the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes. YES. MM.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So she would be alive until Hilda was about two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes. Mm. Oh Hilda - our Hilda remembered her grandma - Speight, being laid on the bed you see.
 And they had to have it - in the - living room because - there were shop you see. They couldn't - have her upstairs and she were there and - it were hard work you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever ask her advice about bringing up your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - I - I d
idn't ask - a lot because - she were nearly all all the - all the tin you know. She'd just say - little bits, because - I don't think she was always in just here you know because she - but she talked very sensible all the time, but there was - I think now
 and again she forgot - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206 just where she were and - mm. E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
h look it's going, are you feeling chilly? Mm. I've never been looking at fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When your children were small can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206 ? Such as, did you feel it neces}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 sary to give them plenty of affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Oh, well - they didn't - we didn't - we - we looked after them and loved 'em but we - you hadn't to - show and - and pet them too much or they don't look after theirself a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What about safety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh they're - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you instruct them carefully about sort of crossing roads and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh - yes, yes, yes, they did, aye, I know when we lived up there and they're coming to school - I always brought them to th
e bottom, every morning. But you see - it were fortunate - they come to me mother's then to their dinner, at what we called dinner time, their lunch time, yes. Then I fetched them back you see at night. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You've already said that with regard to food you liked them to have good plain food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What about discipline, did you have any particular i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206 
deas about discipline with regar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 d to your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - yes, they'll be - oh they knew - they were - I don't think they ever went any
where and were naughty. No. Because we went - we had friends that we went to so or three and they used to say - eeh well, they - they are good up to some, I know, yes. Oh yes, they were taught to - they - not to be rude. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, well they - oh yes, they - they've done - very well, I - I can't think of either growing up but - I think - I don't say that they've had a - bad bringing up. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would they always share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, yes, yes. It weren't - often there were any arguments. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How did you want them to behave toward you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well just to be - only to - just look at you in a right way and - treat you properly and we wanted them to - be brought up same like yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When the children were young did you both ever manage to leave them so that you could go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - we did go now and again but not so often, but if he wanted to go they were willing to - either have them here, or - go to 
my house to look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So it wouldn't be very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, no, we - they didn't go out in those days as they do now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And it was your mother always who was with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. YES? YES. Like - after me mother died like I don't think we - ever have been out much you know, we've never left them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - not a lot because - I think they - I think they get to know too much. They hear it too soon, well - it
's to go setting their little minds - whirling about - something that - that they don't quite understand, I - I think those things are - they've to grow up to 'em and have their own ideas, and views. And I think they've done very well has ours. And I'm no
t grumbling, I think they all - have done - they know their own ideas and - know what to do right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well only to - look after - after themselves and - and - and company. And - and - and loo
k after home and theirselves, that's about - what they were brought up to - main items - and to be nice with people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you tell them that they should hit back or not if another children hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well I - I - I don't think I've got to that, I
've all - I've just said - well you must - what have you been doing, and tried to get to bottom - bottom. I said, well - you - you must stop and not - entertain 'em any further and then they might give up. But I don't think they ever come home with - abov
e one or two complaints. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Was there any other children around where you lived that you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, they - they - I think they - whenever they went out I think - they just sought their own friends and I don't think I
'd - any complaints about - I know mothers come in about their children that I know on, about ours - like some do, they - come to tell you, our so and so's giving him a good knock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You never tried to influence them as to who they should play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, no, they seemed to sort - all very nice friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 If your child}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206 ren did something you disapprove}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 d of what would happen? Would they be smacked or would they be sent upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Eeh I - I don't think they've ever been - I don't remember 'em being sent to bed or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Were they ever smacked at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I - they haven't had many taps I don't think. And I don't think their dad ever did tap one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 On the rare occasion when they were smacked it was you who did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes
, if they're just happen a bit naughty they've had a tap, and it's been - something that - I haven't approved of because - I don't - agree with hitting 'em if they're - just - let them just see - you just want to see what they are up to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Can you remem
ber any particular occasion when Hilda was very small of anything really very naughty that she did which made you smack her? Can you remember any occasion like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I don't. No. No, I don't think I can. I - I don't think I had a lot of trouble with 
them, no, at all. She seemed to be very good at school and - there's always a very nice report all of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both you and your husband or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, I don't think so, they knew how to behave themselves when - their dad were in and - and he thought - a bit of playtime and anything like that it were with him, we threw in together and play like if you - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day? Would you give them a party or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - I - I daresay if a - we tried to - just - they might have had one or two - little friends - to their tea or something, we tried t
o do but - not if they didn't - they always got a bit of something, I don't think their birthdays were ever missed with aunties. No, never. Round this way. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you feel that the teachers would single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, I don't think they - I don't think there's a - they used to call them pets - tea - teacher's pet, well - there might have been - thought so but - I never - I never - I just felt - I can just remember now, I - I used just felt as - ord
inary as the others, I don't think it were, I think it - it were there children themselves if anybody got a - up above, call 'em children's pets. The teacher's pets. Well I don't remember ever - bothering about that at all. No, I don't. I know the - but t
hat was among the children - children themselves, I don't think that - the teachers - no, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Were there any gangs or groups in the school? I mean perhaps from different districts? Do you think the children from a certain area, when they were at school would stick, together in a little group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, I don't think they did, they seemed - they were like from all - over Newsholme way, there were a lot come from over that way, but I think they - might go home together when it were getting darker or like that. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 But they wouldn't stick together at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, no, no, no, there were no stick - they all seemed to be - you'd to do as you were told, march in and happen to your places, not walk about like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Were there any c
hildren that were left out of things at school? Can you remember any child being a bit sort of on the fringe of things and not included?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I don't - I don't think so. No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you go to another school after the church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No. I never went to another school, only this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
If I - for anything I know I was twelve. And the reason I got to leave at twelve - were - I'd - five year - went by your attendances in those days, and I'd five years - full attend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206 anc}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
es. But - if they - some of them - had happen have a - were they - I don't know, if it was a sickness but if you hadn't been to school I don't think it mattered whether you were sick or what, if you hadn't your attend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206 anc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 es they didn't coun
t. And these were from the - were collected up from the education committee. Mm. And I'd five years. At a - I just forget how many - I hadn't many - missing. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you think that you would have stayed longer at school if you had had the opportunity to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - I don't know. Really. There's so many different ways isn't there like and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
But do you think at that time had someone said look you can stay at school for another few years, do you think you would have jumped at it or do you think you were pleased to be able to leave then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, I - I think I - I felt as I ought to be - earning something at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You didn't mind leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, no, I didn't mind, no. No, but - I daresay - there were more brilliant than I were and there were some worse, a lot than I was but -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you go to any part time education afterwards, such as evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I don't - no. No. I - only - only just went to the night school - at evening but that was - wasn't belo
nging the - ordinary school in the time, no. I - I went to night - night - night school at Mechanics it was held, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Two - two hours in evening, I think it was seven 'til nine. You could go agouy three times 
a week but I only, I think I only went once or twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 For how many years did you do this needlework at night school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I went about - I - I know I went two, and then I think I gave up going, 'cos I'd started with music lessons more longer and so -
 I think me mother said I'd better - stop at home more like. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you have any regret a about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no I don't. NO I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, I think - I think you do, I wouldn't 
like - to think any belonging me didn't go to a school, no I wouldn't, I think it - it's a big help in life is - getting to know things at school because you - you learn yourself a bit sometimes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever do a part time job while you were still at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, not as I - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you went straight to full time work, you didn't go half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You went full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes? YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I'd like to ask you about your first full time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - first time -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What was the first job you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Mm. Mm. Going into the spinning at Hattersley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 s. Providence Mill. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What were you doing at Providence Mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well - the first - when you got there - you were put with a person that was spinning. And you'd to 
learn and - with that - person to know how to - stop, the - and - and piece up yourself, and - and put 'em up and then they went up over rollers you know, well, you - I think you were about a week - as we called it learning. Learning to spin, and then}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1574701\charrsid11482206  you started to be a - a doffer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
 next. And that was taking them off. These bobbins - off the spindles. And - you - you went - and that was - the job - well they thought you were perfect - to look after a frame of your own. You see, at the beginning - I - I were 
put up with somebody to learn me. And then - while you're learning and then you see the others coming to doff these - they called it doffing, I don't know what else I could - doffing, take these bobbins off, and I and you put them up on a - on a - rack, y
o
u took 'em off and put 'em up there and it'd be - as quick as possible. As fast as - the faster you could go and better for them. And then - when you got that and - it was generally girls, like, that looked after - these frames. And - then when you learnt
 
and got in the - over - looker's - thought you were - all right to have a - a side of your own, they were - they were called - well you called 'em gates, there were a side at this side and a side at this and - the centre for - was for you, to walk up, and
 - I forget how many spindles, they call 'em, were on a side. And - you got - and then when I were old enough to get - I got a - spinning myself, a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 gait - a gait of me own, as they - as they call it. And then - you - you stopped there, oh and you - and then you could mind three sides - in those days, Hattersley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 s - paid a bit more than Haggas's in wages, three sid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 s, I do remember this at Hattersley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
s, you got ten and six a week. When that was a - and for four sides twelve and six. Well I had - I got three and then I got four, if you could manage the work. And you didn't - you got your wages at that time fortnightly. Not weekly at Hattersley}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 s. I think they did down here. But it - it just felt a nice lot, twenty-five shill - I used - me - I know me mother - I
 - I used to say - are you waiting of it mother? Twenty-five shillings. She used to say, yes, I am. Really. YES.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How did you manage to get the job, did you know someone who worked there? Or did your mother know the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What, that I went dow
n there? Well, there was some just lived down there, at - went - on Oakworth Hall, they were Oakworth - they were Hattersley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 s houses, well - you - had to go to work at Hattersley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
s as a rule, so I went with one of the girls there took me at the beginning to - get to know, I hadn't been in a mill before well, but - I got to like it, yes, I did. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you just got it by yourself, you didn't get it through your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no, no, and I don't - I think - one of these girls asked - the over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 -}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 looker. If I could go start work. And he said yes, and I know I went with them. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What were the hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Six - six - in the morning. Six - I think it - I don't know whether it was eight or half past now, I just forget that for meal, the breakfast. But if it was eight 'til half past you have your breakfast half hour then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You had it at work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, down at the mill, and - and then - you'd half hour then and then if it was half past eight, it would be til half past twelve. You had - co
me home for an hour, I'd come home for me dinner, but I took a bit of breakfast, it was too far - we had a canteen. The - you could have some tea. Yes, in those days. Some nice warm tea. I don't know whether - we'd have paid a ha'penny for a pot or not. -
Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What time wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 ld you finish in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And then - went back for half past one - 'til half past five. - Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And then you had your tea at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. And that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You never worked on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What about Saturday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Saturday? Now I think - well, I were - I once - I won't say whether - it was one o'clock. If it had started - to be half past twelve. If - if I weren't - in the spinning it wasn't long after. That it changed. The time - a bit - sooner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So you used to work every Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, oh yes, yes. Mm. And - there was no - and the - you know, in - in the spinning mills there was always very clean, and the - the floors, well they used to - were - were shiny, all polished. And I can remem
ber all the - girls weren't supposed to do it, but I had to rub up, as we called it. You had a big - lot of wool - that - waste and it had oil on and you had to go up and down, on the floor, on your knees. You should have seen my - and we wore }{
