I - I like - I - at Springhead I had to learn you know, that's how - hard work again learning to weave. But I liked it very much when I got into it. Weaving -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you do any fancy weaving or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I - I rather liked it. It were cloth. Materials you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you do any patterns or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh I didn't do pat - just the plain. Plain weaving - materials.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And you enjoyed doing the weaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you still get on with the people very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, they were - all right you know, you - you've to - like when you've weaving you've to mind your work, you haven't to - time to 
be - staring about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What sort of wages did you get as a weaver, did your pay go up when you became a weaver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well, I did start - pay - paying me mother, for me board. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You stopped giving her all of your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, at twenty-one. But she bought me lots of things beside, I pay - I only paid eight shilling. Paid eight shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And there rest was yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, mm. And you - it - like - if you were - if you got right well going you know - you - I forget how much -
 you'd - you'd - I think you'd earn unto - two pound was a lot I think in them days. Mm. I don't think I earnt so much. No, I shouldn't. But I - I think the good weavers would. And - and on the thick cloth that they earnt a lot more. And I think - Murrell
's - at Howarth - at Hever there, one of my aunts - worked there, and they had a lot - more there because it were heavier material. You work - you were working harder yourself, 'cos it was heavier, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Was it sort of light weight worsteds you were working on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Worsted, yes. Light cloth, you know, for suitings. Yes, good suitings. Well - that used to - I - I've never heard her really tell how much she earned but I know she used to say she earned well. So I think it'd be - fifty shilling or three p
ound in them days at least. Mm. If not more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
When you started to board and just give your mother eight shillings a week, what did you do with the rest of the money, did you spend it or save it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no, I'd to save it, and - and buy - me things, I - I hadn't - I hadn't - I didn't - weren't going to - theatre or anything, no, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Were you buying sort of things for your bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, yes, and - and me mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 bought me - lots of things beside like, yes, oh that's where - yes, that's where mine went. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Have you done any jobs since you were married or have you always been a housewife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
No, I - I've saved - well I - I did happen - go down to Vaile Mills, I did at - when I had our Hilda. But it were only just - to weave - half - happen half a day for me aunt, she worked down there, you could do that in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Give her half a day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Yes, if she want - and I went down to weave for her. And me mother had Hilda I know here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Just half a day a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, oh I didn't go every week. It were just when - when she wanted me, that were all spare time - I never worked, I - I never - never worked no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 That was rather a nice arrangement wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, and then - and Mary - you see, Mary 
were born - during - well, just before he had to go away so I never - I never went to work any more - after - she were - she were - six - six weeks, when he had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 That was into the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Into the Army. Well yes, he - Royal Engineers, he wer
e working - well they were off, he went in the plumbing work you know - in forces. And - but he just got a little bit more money I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Because he was skilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes. Mm. But - and he went away - he went on the fifth of September - and he d
idn't come home - his first leave was six month, they didn't get - so many leaves. And he were - the - year following - he were there - 1917 he went, and he come back in the February 1919. So I know I was here. All the time, wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012630\charrsid11482206 l - I were - were like getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
owt nor save - you couldn't save owt in them days you know. Well he helped to keep me and children did me mother like. I had a bit of a - I had allowance but it didn't go far. Like but - I got on - there'd be lots worse than me, who had nowhere to go.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Looking back to the time when you were working, do you think you would have preferred another occupation other than in the mill? Do you think there was something you would have liked to have done better than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, I don't think so, I - I enj
oyed me life for anything I know with it. We seemed to go round - here when you - all your friends are brought up in that way you seemed to - I think you enjoyed it better, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 They weren't organised then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Did you feel when you were working that there were divisions of interest among the workers? Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and people who weren't trained.
