\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, yes, she'd come here, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you have any special friends at that time, either boyfriends or girlfriends? Did you have perhaps just one or two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh - only just one - Jennie that I've gone with all the - yes, all - yes, all from school like, mm. I didn't have any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Then you went out with Jennie where would you go to with her, would you just visit each other's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, that's - about where we went, or go for a walk. Mm. On top there
 and back, that were our general walk. Occasionally, often - not often - happen go to Keighley and one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 What would you do at Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Just look at the shops, that's all, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And your parents always met your friends did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did they always expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh - no, no, I - I - could always tell - honestly where I'd been, I'd been somewhere I shouldn't have been. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did they always question you, would they always ask you where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, not a lot - no, I weren't - questioned a lot, not that way at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did they insist you being home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh well I hadn't to be in late. No. Well - oh when I were courting it had to be nine o'clock. I 
think it'd be eight when I were younger, no later than eight or half past. Mm. He - had to be in at nine o'clock then. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How old were you when you got married? Did you say twenty-four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Twenty-four. Mm, twenty-four when I were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 How long had you known your husband, you knew him all your life more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, yes, yes, I have, at school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And he came from the same village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. Yes. He'd only two months - he's two months younger than I. Yes. He - he'll be eighty-one
 in June, and I'm eighty-one at second of April in a fortnight. All being well. There's only those - months in our ages, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You've already told me that you had a bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you save up some money before you got married as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Well I tried - I tried to - to do, but I - I know I had - I hadn't a right lot because you hadn't had chance to - your wage - like - we had just a - you used to call for children, your money boxes, if anybody gave you owt, well - if we had 
- when we had those money boxes, they were emptied out as a rule for our - new clothes. Clothes time. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 So although you had a bottom drawer with things in it-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You didn't have much money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No. No, I had - I - I did have a - a bank book and then I - I don't know, it were drawn out or something 'cos - some clothes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You said that your mother used to buy odds and ends to put in your bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did she help you in any other way in setting up a home, did she give you any assistance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, when - oh yes, I got lots of - things - when - when I were married? Yes, yes. Oh I got lots of things, mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you get engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Get engaged? I didn't get a - engagement ring. No. No I didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Could you describe your wedding? Did you have a big wedding or a little wedding? Did you just have your close relatives at the wedding?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Quiet wedding, that's all we had yes, mm, mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Just your close relatives would it be? Just your relatives and one or two friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, that's all. Mm, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you get any nice presents when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh yes, I did at the time but I've forgot. Like there's a lot of them - I've got the most beautiful - there used to be plush table c
overs you know, a green one. From my aunt at Howarth, and it - well it were really - a lovely thing it were. And it's only - a year or two back - my - best - counterpane - me mother bought me, that it - our Margaret has it for an ironing cloth now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 That was a wedding present was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, and that's so old and it were - were lovely. Mm. Oh I got a lot of nice - and I told you - I were telling you over Mr Wright, I thought he was a nice gentleman, he bought me - the spoons, and from shop and it's g
ot pulled down this last two or three year, down Low Street. I forget what it were, it - were below Barwick and Haggas's, it were the other side of road. And - I know I - I had the box not long ago, mm. Oh I got lots of - of things bought. I got some - pi
ctures, you know, and I've gone right off pictures. And - and I used to like - like them but - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Did you have a honeymoon or did you go straight to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Oh no, no, no, we didn't have a honeymoon. There weren't many - I don't think there were many honeymoons in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Where did you live once you got married? Did you live with your parents or did you get a house of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 We got a house, we just lived up Lidget Hill at that time. Lidget Hill, mm. But - you see - I didn
't stop - we didn't stop long up there, at that end. Because up at this end - I lived up - you know, I told you about Grey Scar? About - where you go on to - chemical - on there, there's two cottages in the field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Where your uncles lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 The - 
the - my - that were my uncles' property, you see, and - this house came empty. They did call for me and - well asked me if I would go. And - and me mother wanted me to go, she didn't like that end. She used to think - she said - she felt more at home at 
this end. So how I'll be - I lived up there - when he had to go soldier - well our Mary was born up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Up Grey Scar?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes, at Bostin Hill. It was called Bostin Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 That's Lidget is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 No, no, this up here. That was Lidget Hill. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Bo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14753009\charrsid11482206 sto}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
n Hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14753009\charrsid11482206 Bosto}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
n Hill. Mm. Mary were born there. And - we'd lived there you see - well - hadn't lived there above two years I don't think when he had to go - soldiering you see and - and it - it were all done nicely through for me did - m
e Uncle - get - wanted me to go and - and - the family seemed to think I ought to take it, yet I only paid half a crown a rent a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And it was your uncle's house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. And so - and I stopped there - up to me - up there, we lived up the
re after he come back - from the war you see. 'Til - me mother died. And me mother died - it were - on the first - her had a sad do, it were first of February me mother died, suddenly, and it were our wedding day - anniversary on the second. But - and so 
-
 you see, I - up there and me father were here at home, and two lads. And he wanted me to - to come you know back and look after 'em. Well I never thought you see, you - you don't think at that time with that worry. I were - I didn't - I - you know, I wan
t
ed to come, as felt as I ought to look after 'em. Never thought about the future. But - it - you've live to see that you see. And I didn't - he said, well you can please yourself. About going, but I - I'll go with you. But - I aren't going willingly. See,
 
I'd rather have had me own home. And so I couldn't see no other way, but - you do see after. Because it were only about two - two or three years after me - someone told me me father - they'd seen me father with a woman, well it were all right but you know
,
 I - something happen feel right to another woman but - I couldn't feel - my mother - seemed to be my mother all time you know but they don't stop at home in like - we had to do, well I think you get more attached when you're - in the older days to your o
w
n parents, than they do now, because - they're in and out that much, well they get a lot of friends, I - I don't - I don't say they don't think about their parents, but I don't think they go as deep down - as we did in our time and so - well that - so whe
n
 - after that you know - I - I weren't happy - here. Didn't feel happy and so - I went - I went with children - to his sister's for a few days. To Hull. And when I came back - he said, oh I'd such a shock when - he never said owt to me, he says, well I've
 
got - I've got me cottage. He said - he - never - he hadn't troubled me with it, he says, I - I don't feel as I can live here he says, I don't feel right now. And so he - he - they - they must have just have had a word or two with father and him while I w
e
re off. And so - he says - but he says, I - I'm going. And he says, you can please yourself, if you want to stop with the children it's all right to me. I'll support you just the same. I'll look after you but - he says, I can't stop here. Well you know it
 nearly broke my heart.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 You had to choose between the two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes, and so - I will be - I says, well - I says, if you're going - you're going to go I shall have to go, I'm forced to follow you. I says, it's my duty. So we went - on - Clough houses,
 you know, on Mill Lane, from your house you can see those cottages, when the fields are - bare. Well, we lived on - our Mary were - our Margaret were born on there. Mm. We went on there. We were happy enough like and it were - you see, it all went all ri
g
ht, me father got married you know and - she come here and - and then it - she found it out were too big a house you see do you follow, for two. So he come and asked me - if I'd like to buy it. I says, well, I says, we haven't money just yet. But - he sai
d
, well would I rent it. And I says yes, I says, we'll rent it. And he says, anything that - you want to do in it will you - we wanted a bathroom, we hadn't one then, but in between, when it was empty - dad started a bathroom you see, mm, took it off the b
ack bedroom, and we had toilet - a toilet put in upstairs as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Would it be within the period before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Well now, it - it's above - well our Margaret's - forty-three now. And she were born in that Clough
 houses. So it won't - we'd gone before then on there. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 It would be late in the twenties I think, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14753009\charrsid11482206 E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 h - I just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 About 1929?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Mm. I daresay it would be, mm. And so - and it were - all - all right, we paid rent, to me father 
like. Mm. So it were all right, he were all right but - it - it were - I think that were one of biggest - troubles of mine like. Mm. But - and so - he were willing to come back and so - we rented it. So it - I says, well - I says - if we pay for it we'll 
have it some time. So we did, I'm telling you like. In confidence. Well it was when - they owned the row, the bank - where penny bank was. Well the bank wanted to buy it. The - and they sold it to the bank. Well he got his share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Your husband got his share?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Share - his share of it because he were - he were partner. The other partner and there were the builder, and - so that's how we - we bought this house, mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 I'm really more concerned about where you lived before 1919. It sounds as it until 1919 you lived up Lidget Hill in a rented house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 And then you lived at the little lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 In your uncles' house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 Yes. We - we wasn't up Lidget long. No, we didn't do - we just made it our home really. But we hadn't done anything in it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 When your husband came out of the army, you were still living up this little lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2256154 ES  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649235\charrsid11482206 
Yes. Oh yes, when - we kept the house on 'til he come back - from war. YES? Because I - you see, I - I - when he went - on fifth of Septem
ber, it was on a Wednesday - I - I just - were up there with children and me father and mother come up at night. And they says - oh you can't stop here by yourself. And so I said, well I'll try it tonight. But I never slept a wink. And so they come up of 
